IFC emerging market index down 0 . 3 pct at 330 . 62 . The International Finance Corporation ' s composite index of emerging market equities , denominated in dollars IFC / IPRD , fell 0 . 3 percent to 330 . 62 at midsession on Monday . Latin America edged down 0 . 8 percent day - on - day to 624 . 63 , Asia was up 0 . 5 percent at 269 . 09 and Europe , Middle East and Africa were down 1 . 2 percent at 158 . 90 . The IFC composite index began 1997 at 294 . 37 , after making gains of 7 . 0 percent over the course of 1996 . ING Barings ' Global Emerging Market Index ( BEMI ) , also denominated in dollars BFFO , was up 0 . 04 percent day - on - day at 177 . 87 at 1245 GMT . It began 1997 at 159 . 57 after rising 8 . 9 percent over the course of 1996 . Morgan Stanley ' s dollar - denominated Emerging Markets Free index was up 0 . 22 percent at 529 . 859 , calculated after the close of trade on Friday . It began 1997 at 476 . 315 after making gains of 3 . 9 percent over 1996 . All indices are capitalisation - weighted and are calculated daily . The IFC index measures returns on equities , liquid and accessible to foreign investors , from 30 emerging market countries after adding Russia , Slovakia , Egypt and Morocco on February 3 . It is updated at 2300 GMT . The BEMI index measures equity returns without dividends from some 21 emerging market countries , with the latest changes reported by 0900 GMT . The MSCI Free measures equity returns without dividends from 26 emerging market nations . Changes are reported at 1300 GMT . The J . P . Morgan emerging market bond index ELMI , its returns calculated in dollar terms , fell 0 . 42 percent to 126 . 51 by the start of trade on Monday . It began 1997 at 124 . 83 after making gains of 14 . 86 percent over 1996 . By region , Latin America was down 1 . 37 percent at 104 . 84 , Asia fell 0 . 02 to 133 . 32 and East Europe was down 0 . 22 at 158 . 30 . - - Caroline Brothers , London Newsroom + 44 171 542 2734 
